### üìà **Detailed Statistical Analysis**

#### **Civic Character Score Comparison**

The descriptive statistics reveal starkly different civic profiles between the conservative/institutional (McCain) and progressive/populist (Sanders) speeches. McCain's speech shows high scores in virtues and low scores in vices, leading to high tension scores and a high overall CCI. Sanders' speech shows high scores in both a key virtue (Justice) and several vices (Tribalism, Resentment), resulting in low tension and a low CCI.

| Speaker (Ideology)      | Dignity | Tribalism | Justice | Resentment | Hope | Fear | Pragmatism | **CCI** |
| ----------------------- | :-----: | :-------: | :-----: | :--------: | :--: | :--: | :--------: | :-----: |
| **McCain** (Conservative) |  0.85   |   0.20    |  0.75   |    0.15    | 0.90 | 0.05 |    0.70    | **0.68** |
| **Sanders** (Progressive) |  0.80   |   0.60    |  0.90   |    0.70    | 0.40 | 0.30 |    0.30    | **0.16** |

